All conditioned dharmas are momentary (kṣaṇika).

A dharma arises, functions, and ceases within a single instant (kṣaṇa).



ayatana -> base sense
dhatu -> sense object
vijñana -> sense consciousness
sparsa -> contact
vedana -> feeling
sankhara -> mental formation
manas -> reflection / citta -> conscious reflection



qué significa que sparsa y ear consciousness ocurran simultáneamente

Simultaneity

In Abhidharma, sparśa co-arises with ear-consciousness.
Your current code uses &&, which is fine logically, but keep in mind that both must be true in the same instant to match the doctrinal model.
